            <title>[HBASE-454] Holding an HConnection open through an hbase restart doesn&apos;t work</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-454</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a java tools server that uses some hbase client functionality (it is a servlet: in doGet I create a new HTable and call HTable.get).  However, if I restart hbase, then subsequent hbase calls take forever.  To fix it, I have to restart my java tools server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suspect it is caching the old location of .META., and can&apos;t deal with the cache being wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
